[00:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Hello and welcome to this Resolum 7.24 release video. In this video, we\'ll have a look at all the new features in this release. In the past couple of releases, we have focused on composition loading. Loading large compositions is now faster'

[00:12] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'than it\'s ever been. As an additional help, you can now see in the title bar whether Arena is busy with opening, saving, or closing a composition. Additional speed upgrades are made to'

[00:24] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'the MIDI implementation. Sending and receiving MIDI has never been faster in both Arena, Avenue, and Wire. Additionally, you can now pause and resume the medi monitor for an easier'

[00:37] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'debugging experience. Resolum now supports 10 bit colors. With more and more lead screens, projectors, and live shows supporting or requiring 10- bit colors, we have made a jump to'

[00:50] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: '10 bit as well. There are a lot of variables involved to make sure your entire pipeline from laptop to screen is 10 bit. Check out the support article linked in the video description to learn more. It is also good to mention here as'

[01:03] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'well that wire monitors are now 10 bit by default. One of our codesmiths at Resolum HQ has cooked up a pretty cool CRT effect you can use in Arena and Avenue to bathe yourself in the vintage'

[01:17] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'vibes of classic CRT displays. This effect is a wire patch, so feel free to open it up and customize it to your liking. Talking about wire, let\'s check out what is new in our favorite patching'

[01:29] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'environment. The notes panel has made it over from Arena to Wire. This is perfect for jotting down code, ids, or to-do list right from inside your patch. The navigator panel is new to Wire and'

[01:43] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'allows for quick navigation through big patches. Note previews are now visual, so you can instantly see your textures, shapes, slices, and geometry by hovering over'

[01:55] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'inlets or outlets. The texture from data node has gotten an update and now supports two-dimensional textures by setting a stride value. Check out our new texture from data'

[02:07] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'tutorial to learn more. Complementing the last change, there is the introduction of the Gaussian node. With this node, you can do a gaussian function on float and float two values to create a whole new range of visuals.'

[02:20] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'A new suite of cylindrical and spherical nodes have been added. The from node allow you to turn cylindrical and spherical coordinates into cartisian coordinates, which is a very nerdy way'

[02:32] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'of saying you can now generate sphere and cylinder coordinates. Inserting nodes got a lot better this update. You can now insert notes in between multicord in or outlets just like this.'

[02:46] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Check out our inserting nodes tutorial to learn more. As requested by the community, we have ported over the kaleidoscope effect from arena and avenue to wire. We hope you will have'

[02:58] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'fun with this new release. Make sure to tag us in your projects on the socials and keep an eye out for tutorials on our new features.'
